---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

export const meta = {
  title: "EBITDA vs Revenue: Valuing a Business",
  description: "Understand the difference between EBITDA and Revenue. See a visual income statement waterfall from top-line revenue down to EBITDA.",
  category: "guide",
  published: "2026-03-17",
};

const schema = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "EBITDA vs Revenue: Valuing a Business",
    "description": "Understand the difference between EBITDA and Revenue. See a visual income statement waterfall from top-line revenue down to EBITDA.",
    "author": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Westmount Fundamentals"
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Is revenue the same as EBITDA?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                  "@type": "Answer",
                  "text": "No, revenue is the total money brought in by sales ('top line'). EBITDA is the profit left over after subtracting the direct costs of those sales and operating expenses ('bottom line' proxy)."
            }
      },
      {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Why value a company on EBITDA instead of Revenue?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                  "@type": "Answer",
                  "text": "Two companies with the same revenue might have vastly different profit margins. Valuing on EBITDA accounts for operating efficiency, ensuring you pay for actual cash generation, not just sales volume."
            }
      },
      {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Can EBITDA ever be higher than Revenue?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                  "@type": "Answer",
                  "text": "In normal operations, no. EBITDA is calculated by subtracting expenses from revenue, so it will always be lower than revenue unless there is a massive, unusual one-time gain classified as operating income."
            }
      }
]
  }
];
---

<SiteLayout site="westmount" title={meta.title} description={meta.description} canonical="https://westmountfundamentals.com/ebitda-vs-revenue" schema={schema}>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>EBITDA vs Revenue: Valuing a Business</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Understand the difference between EBITDA and Revenue. See a visual income statement waterfall from top-line revenue down to EBITDA.</p>
    </div>


    <div class="explainer">
      <h2>Why EBITDA matters more than Revenue for Valuation</h2>
      <p>Revenue is simply the total amount of money a company brings in from sales. It tells you nothing about how much it costs to generate those sales. A company doing $100M in revenue might be losing money every year, while a company doing $20M in revenue might be incredibly profitable. Therefore, valuations are typically based on earnings (like EBITDA), not just revenue.</p>

      <h2>The Income Statement Waterfall</h2>
      <p>To understand where EBITDA sits in relation to Revenue, look at the standard income statement flow:</p>

      <div class="waterfall" style="background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 8px; padding: 2rem; margin: 2rem 0;">
        <div style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.2rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Gross Revenue</div>
        <div style="margin-left: 20px; color: #ef4444;">- Cost of Goods Sold (COGS)</div>
        <div style="font-weight: bold; margin: 10px 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding-top: 10px;">= Gross Profit</div>
        <div style="margin-left: 20px; color: #ef4444;">- Operating Expenses (SG&A, R&D, excluding D&A)</div>
        <div style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--accent-color); margin: 10px 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding-top: 10px;">= EBITDA</div>
        <div style="margin-left: 20px; color: #ef4444;">- Depreciation & Amortization</div>
        <div style="font-weight: bold; margin: 10px 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding-top: 10px;">= EBIT (Operating Income)</div>
        <div style="margin-left: 20px; color: #ef4444;">- Interest Expense</div>
        <div style="margin-left: 20px; color: #ef4444;">- Taxes</div>
        <div style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.2rem; margin: 10px 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding-top: 10px;">= Net Income (The Bottom Line)</div>
      </div>

      <p>As you can see, EBITDA is roughly halfway down the income statement. It's the profit after the direct costs of running the business, but before the financial and accounting costs.</p>
    </div>
<section class="related-guides">
  <h2>Related EBITDA Guides</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/ebitda-calculator">EBITDA Calculator</a></li>
    <li><a href="/what-is-ebitda-margin">What is EBITDA Margin?</a></li>
    <li><a href="/ebitda-vs-net-income">EBITDA vs Net Income</a></li>
    <li><a href="/adjusted-ebitda">Adjusted EBITDA Explained</a></li>
    <li><a href="/debt-to-ebitda-ratio">Debt to EBITDA Ratio</a></li>
    <li><a href="/good-ebitda-margin">What is a Good EBITDA Margin?</a></li>
    <li><a href="/ev-ebitda-sectors">EV/EBITDA by Sector</a></li>
  </ul>
</section>    <section class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <details>
        <summary>Is revenue the same as EBITDA?</summary>
        <p>No, revenue is the total money brought in by sales ('top line'). EBITDA is the profit left over after subtracting the direct costs of those sales and operating expenses ('bottom line' proxy).</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Why value a company on EBITDA instead of Revenue?</summary>
        <p>Two companies with the same revenue might have vastly different profit margins. Valuing on EBITDA accounts for operating efficiency, ensuring you pay for actual cash generation, not just sales volume.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Can EBITDA ever be higher than Revenue?</summary>
        <p>In normal operations, no. EBITDA is calculated by subtracting expenses from revenue, so it will always be lower than revenue unless there is a massive, unusual one-time gain classified as operating income.</p>
      </details>
    </section>

    <style is:inline>
      .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
      .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
      .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
      .subtitle { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.1rem; }

      .calculator-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
      @media (min-width: 768px) { .calculator-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; } }

      .card { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 2rem; }
      .calc-header { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding-bottom: 1rem; }
      .calc-header h2 { font-size: 1.4rem; margin: 0 0 0.25rem 0; }
      .calc-header p { margin: 0; color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.9rem; }

      .input-group { margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
      .input-group label { display: block; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.95rem; }
      input { background: var(--bg-color); color: var(--text-primary); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 0.75rem 1rem; border-radius: 8px; width: 100%; font-size: 1rem; }
      input:focus { outline: none; border-color: var(--accent-color); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-color) 20%, transparent); }

      .result-card { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-color) 10%, transparent); border: 1px solid var(--accent-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin-top: 2rem; text-align: center; }
      .result-card.secondary { background: color-mix(in srgb, #10b981 10%, transparent); border-color: #10b981; }
      .result-card h3 { margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0; font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--text-secondary); }
      .result-value { font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--accent-color); }
      .secondary .result-value { color: #10b981; }

      .explainer { margin: 3rem 0; line-height: 1.6; }
      .explainer h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin: 2rem 0 1rem; }
      .explainer h3 { font-size: 1.4rem; margin: 1.5rem 0 0.75rem; }
      .explainer p { margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--text-secondary); }
      .explainer ul { margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--text-secondary); padding-left: 1.5rem; }
      .explainer li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }

      .data-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 2rem 0; background: var(--card-bg); border-radius: 8px; overflow: hidden; box-shadow: 0 4px 6px -1px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); }
      .data-table th, .data-table td { padding: 1rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
      .data-table th { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-color) 10%, transparent); font-weight: bold; }
      .data-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }

      .related-guides { margin: 4rem 0; padding: 2rem; background: var(--card-bg); border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
      .related-guides h2 { margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; font-size: 1.5rem; }
      .related-guides ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 1rem; }
      @media (min-width: 600px) { .related-guides ul { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; } }
      .related-guides a { color: var(--accent-color); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; padding: 0.5rem; display: block; border-radius: 6px; transition: background 0.2s; }
      .related-guides a:hover { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-color) 10%, transparent); }

      .faq-section { margin-top: 3rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding-top: 2rem; }
      .faq-section h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
      .faq-section details { margin: 1rem 0; padding: 1rem; background: var(--card-bg); border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
      .faq-section summary { font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; }
      .faq-section details p { margin: 1rem 0 0 0; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.5; }

      .formula-visual { text-align: center; margin: 3rem 0; }
      .visual-boxes { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 1rem; margin: 1rem 0; }
      .visual-boxes .box { background: var(--card-bg); padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); font-weight: bold; min-width: 100px; }
      .visual-boxes .box.highlight { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-color) 10%, transparent); border-color: var(--accent-color); color: var(--accent-color); }
      .visual-boxes .math-op { font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: bold; }
    </style>
  </div>
</SiteLayout>
